Comment (src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue:1042):
`openJobDetail()` has no guard against overlapping requests. If a user clicks two different jobs quickly, the slower response can overwrite `jobDetail` after `selectedJobId` has changed, showing the wrong job details in the drawer. Consider using the same request-sequence pattern as `loadJobs()` (or an AbortController) and only applying the response if it matches the latest requested job id/sequence.
