Comment (src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue:1068):
`loadDiagnostics()` can be triggered multiple times (tab activation, select changes, and the Run button) but doesn’t guard against concurrent in-flight requests. A slower request can overwrite `diagnostics` with stale results after the user selects a different notification type. Use a request sequence / cancellation approach similar to `loadJobs()` so only the latest request updates state.

