Implementation guidance: In src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue, add a diagnostics request sequence variable near jobsRequestSequence, e.g. let diagnosticsRequestSequence = 0. In loadDiagnostics(), capture const requestSequence = ++diagnosticsRequestSequence and const notificationName = diagnosticsNotificationName.value before building the URL. Use notificationName in the encoded diagnostics endpoint so the request is tied to the selection at invocation time. After axios.get resolves, only assign diagnostics.value if requestSequence is still the latest and diagnosticsNotificationName.value still equals notificationName. In catch, only assign diagnosticsError.value under that same guard. In finally, only set diagnosticsLoading.value = false if the request is current. Preserve the existing behavior of clearing diagnostics and errors when a new latest request starts.
